message.content:
A 'Symphyotrichum lateriflorum' is a perennial flowering plant, belonging to the aster family.
It grows to a height of 1-3 feet and has alternate leaves which are narrow with pointed tips.
The flowers of the 'Symphyotrichum lateriflorum' are small and numerous, with white petals and yellow centers.
The plant blooms in late summer to early fall.
It is commonly found in wetlands, meadows, and along the edges of forests, especially in eastern North America.
The plant has a variety of medicinal uses among Indigenous peoples, including treatment for skin conditions and fevers.
Due to its attractive flowers, 'Symphyotrichum lateriflorum' is also commonly used as an ornamental plant in gardens.
